## Architecture

### The packages

```
packages/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ fleet/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ control/       ‚Üê Control plane + per-machine agent (same binary family)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ topology/      ‚Üê Static fleet topology config (seed.config.json deployment)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ssh/           ‚Üê Helpers for direct SSH access to fleet machines
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sync/          ‚Üê Cross-machine git sync utilities
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ memory/            ‚Üê Memory service (workload: installed on ren1)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ heartbeat/         ‚Üê Identity heartbeat loop (for Ren)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core/              ‚Üê Shared boot contract (BOOT.md lives here)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hosts/             ‚Üê Host adapters (claude, codex, gemini CLIs)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ inference/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router/        ‚Üê Fleet router (workload: installed on ren3)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ jury/          ‚Üê Ensemble consensus (multi-model fan-out + aggregation)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ queue/         ‚Üê Inference queue ‚Äî WIP
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sensitivity/   ‚Üê Sensitivity classification for routing
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils/         ‚Üê Shared inference utilities
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ providers/         ‚Üê Model provider adapters
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ skills/            ‚Üê Shared skills
```

**The two things in production today:**
- **`packages/fleet/control/`** ‚Äî produces `seed-agent`, `seed-cli`, `seed-control-plane` binaries. The agent runs on every fleet machine; the control plane runs on one (ren2); the CLI runs anywhere an operator types.
- **`packages/memory/`** ‚Äî produces `seed-memory` binary + a launchd plist template, packaged into workload artifact bundles (`memory-<ver>-<target>.tar.gz`).

### Core concepts

| Concept | What it is | Example |
|---|---|---|
| **Machine** | A host in the fleet, running a seed-agent | ren1, ren2, ren3 |
| **Agent** | The per-machine daemon ‚Äî WebSocket to control plane, health reports, command execution, workload convergence | `com.seed.agent` |
| **Control plane** | Central brain ‚Äî stores config, dispatches commands, serves REST API + WebSocket | ren2:4310 |
| **Service** | An externally-installed process seed only health-probes | `ollama` on ren1 |
| **Workload** | An artifact bundle seed installs + supervises itself | `memory@0.2.0`, `fleet-router@0.3.0` |
| **Model** | Tenant data loaded by a workload's runtime | `qwen3-embedding:0.6b` |

See `docs/workloads-design.md` for the full workloads design.

### Protocols

- **Agent ‚Üî Control plane:** WebSocket, agent-initiated. Messages are typed (`AnnounceMessage`, `HealthMessage`, `CommandEnvelope`, `ConfigUpdateMessage`, etc. in `packages/fleet/control/src/types.ts`).
- **Operator ‚Üî Control plane:** REST API over HTTP, bearer token auth (`SEED_OPERATOR_TOKEN`).
- **Workload artifacts:** tarballs fetched by the agent. Phase 1 supports `file://` URLs; Phase 2 will support `https://` (GitHub Releases).

### Key design decisions (in `docs/design-decisions.md`)

1. Control plane runs on one always-on machine (ren2). Operators connect to it; agents connect outbound to it.
2. Agents use outbound WebSockets ‚Äî no SSH key distribution, NAT-friendly.
3. Canonical config lives in the control plane's SQLite, not git.
4. **No LLM calls in fleet management** ‚Äî decision #6. The management path is $0.
5. Each release is a single tag (`v*.*.*`); all binaries ship together with checksums.
6. Workloads are declaratively converged, not imperatively installed.

